core.conflict

Class AbstractConflictScope<T,E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.conflict.AbstractConflictScope<T,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of entities that define this conflict scope.
    E - The type of entities that underly the conflict incurred by the conflict source entity of this conflict scope.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IConflictScope<T,E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GeneralizationAdaptationClassAssociationConflictScope, GeneralizationAdaptationClassAttributeConflictScope, GeneralizationAdaptationClassDependencyConflictScope

    public abstract class AbstractConflictScope<T,E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IConflictScope<T,E>
    an AbstractConflictScope generic abstract class that is used to factor the common interface and state of all concrete conflict scope classes.

    It must be specialized by all concrete conflict scope classes.
    Author:
    Bachar Rima
    See Also:
    IConflictDomain, AbstractConflictSource
